{{Quote|What should my comm sign be? Oh, I know. Jedi Two checking in.|[[Neel]]|<ref name="SC 101">{{SkeletonCrew|This Could Be a Real Adventure}}</ref>}}
Throughout [[the galaxy]], individuals such as [[pilot]]s used '''callsigns''',<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref> also known as a '''call sign''',<ref name="Master of Evil">''[[Master of Evil]]''</ref> or '''comm signs''',<ref name="SC 101" /> to identify themselves as a means of saving [[time]] in communication and avoiding confusion. [[Red Leader]] was an example of a callsign,<ref name="ANH" /> as were [[Blade Leader]],<ref name="blade">{{InsiderCite|issue1=149|issue2=150|Blade Squadron (short story)}}</ref> [[Victor Two]], and [[Victor Three]].<ref name="Battlefront">''[[Star Wars Battlefront]]''</ref>

